title: Section 110(5) of US Copyright Act
status_description: If the Member concerned does not comply with the DSB recommendations and rulings within the prescribed time, the complainant may request permission to impose retaliation measures (suspend concessions or other obligations) against the respondent.  If the respondent disagrees on the level (value) and/or sector of retaliation, arbitration may be requested under Article 22.6 or 22.7 of the DSU.  This category includes both (1) disputes currently undergoing Art. 22.6 arbitration, and (2) disputes where a request to retaliate has been made, but arbitration has not started.

title: Sunset Reviews of Anti-Dumping Measures on Oil Country Tubular Goods from Argentina
short_title: US — Oil Country Tubular Goods Sunset Reviews
status_description: If the Member concerned does not comply with the DSB recommendations and rulings within the prescribed time, the complainant may request permission to impose retaliation measures (suspend concessions or other obligations) against the respondent.  If the respondent disagrees on the level (value) and/or sector of retaliation, arbitration may be requested under Article 22.6 or 22.7 of the DSU.  This category includes both (1) disputes currently undergoing Art. 22.6 arbitration, and (2) disputes where a request to retaliate has been made, but arbitration has not started.

status_description: If the Member concerned does not comply with the DSB recommendations and rulings within the prescribed time, the complainant may request permission to impose retaliation measures (suspend concessions or other obligations) against the respondent.
